# Cursor AI Configuration Rules

## Agent Configuration
This project uses DeepSeek and Qwen APIs as agents in Cursor AI.

### Environment Variables
- `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY`: Your DeepSeek API key from .env
- `QWEN_API_KEY`: Your Qwen API key from .env

### Agent Settings
- **Primary Agent**: DeepSeek (deepseek-chat model)
- **Fallback Agent**: Qwen (qwen-turbo model)
- **Model Selection**: Use based on task complexity and availability

### Configuration Files
- `.cursor/agents.json`: Agent definitions and settings
- `.env`: API keys (ensure DEEPSEEK_API_KEY and QWEN_API_KEY are set)

### How to Use
1. Set DEEPSEEK_API_KEY in .env
2. Set QWEN_API_KEY in .env
3. Restart Cursor IDE
4. Select preferred agent in Cursor settings

### Fallback Behavior
- If DeepSeek is unavailable, Qwen will be used
- Both agents support streaming responses
- Timeout set to 30 seconds per request
